# OpenAI Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from your Supabase project settings: https://supabase.com/dashboard
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (cp env.example .env)
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys and URLs
# 3. Never commit the .env file to version control (it's already in .gitignore)
#
# OpenAI Setup:
# - Sign up at https://platform.openai.com/
# - Navigate to API Keys section
# - Create a new API key
# - Copy the key and paste it as the value for VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY
#
# Supabase Setup:
# - Sign up at https://supabase.com/
# - Create a new project
# - Go to Settings > API
# - Copy the Project URL and anon/public key
# - Paste them as values for VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# Security Note:
# These environment variables are exposed client-side due to the VITE_ prefix.
# For production, consider moving API calls to a backend server.
